Hi,There is no file I can attach to reproduce the error. The Excelfile is produced by a program.This is what happens:do while (sql select statement) { 1. execute sql select statment n. 2. check if excel file exist, if so read the file. 3. create a new excelsheet from sql result, and append it to the excelfile. 4. save the excelfile.}The program code creating the excelsheet is huge.I attach the code responsible for 2,3 and 4 below. The 'interesting' code are in between the comments: // Insert title row  ...// Add data rows

For each but the first SQL, the Excel file is read by the reader. For some reason, the reader only regards the attributes from the last sheet. You should be able to reproduce this error with any excel file with more than one sheet. I set the following attributes for the first row in each sheet:setName('Arial');setBold(true);setUnderline(PHPExcel_Style_Font::UNDERLINE_SINGLE);setARGB(PHPExcel_Style_Color::COLOR_BLUE);

If you process such an excel sheet by the reader i.e.   $objReader1 = new PHPExcel_Reader_Excel2007; $objPHPExcel = $objReader1->load("EXCELFILE");

you should loose the attribute of all sheets but the last one.

I hope this is something you can work on. I attach a produced excelfile, (please remove the file when you have download it) This excel file misses attributes on all but the last two sheets.I suspect that if you process this excel file by the loader it will only have attribute left on the last sheet.

<<?php/*** SQL result converter - dynamically included in function {@link execSql()}** This SQL converter converts a mysqli select result into a Excel 2007 worksheet.* This code is a wrapper to the program product {@link http://www.codeplex.com/PHPExcel/Wiki/View.aspx PHP Excel 2007 classes}* This program product was originally developed by {@link http://www.balliauw.be/maarten Maarten Balliauw}** I assembled this code by looking at some examples in the Tests directory. You should probably enjoy the {@link sqlconverter_default.php adac default sql converter documentation} first, before you digest this.** Processing: * 1 - Initializing, we set up constants, check for file(s) existance etc.* 2 - Get meta data from the result set.* 3 - Include necessary PHP Excel 2007 classes files. For reasons not clear to me yet, I have to change include-path and set PWD to install library of PHP Excel 2007 classes to get things going. (I reset those before saving the Excel sheet.)* 4 - Create the Excel sheet* 5 - Post-edit the Excel sheet and save** @see sqlconverter_default.php, for a details on sql converters* @author Lasse Johansson <lars.a.johansson@se.atlascopco.com>* @version  1.0.0* @package adac* @subpackage sqlconverter* @uses getCustomXml()*/

